    <div class="alpheios-lex-entry" lemma-id="n4984" body-key="α">
          <b><span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">κάμνω</span></b> , fut. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">καμεῖται</span>, aor. 2. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἔκαμον, κάμε</span>, subj. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">κάμῃσι</span>, perf. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">κέκμηκα</span>,
          part. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">κεκμηώς, -ηῶτα, -ηότας</span>, mid.
          aor. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἐκάμοντο, καμόμεσθα</span>: I. intr.,
            <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">grow weary</span>, frequently w. acc. of specification,
            <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">γυῖα, ὦμον, χεῖρα</span>, also w. thing as
          subj., <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">πόδες, ὄσσε</span>, <i><span class="en">Od. 12.232</span></i>; w. part., <i><span class="en">Il. 4.244</span></i>, <i><span class="en">Il.
            7.5</span></i>; euphem., <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">καμόντες</span>, the
            <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">dead</span>, those who have finished their toil, <i><span class="en">Od. 11.476</span></i>.— II. trans. (aor. act.),
            <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">wrought</span> with toil, <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">μίτρη, τὴν
            χαλκῆες κάμον ἄνδρες</span>, <i><span class="en">Il.
            4.187</span></i>; also with <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">τεύχων</span>; aor.
          mid., ‘won by toil,’ <i><span class="en">Il. 18.341</span></i>;
          ‘worked up for oneself,’ ‘tilled,’ <i><span class="en">Od.
            9.130</span></i>.</div> <div class="alpheios-lex-footnotes en"> </div>
